Set 2 may need to have flute and trombone parts revised, and includes alternate glockenspiel part and celeste part marked "probably not needed". Part counts in instrumentation box refer only to Set 1. This music was originally a film scoring cue called "Vacation In Sussex" for "The Americanization Of Emily" When MF prepared for performance in Pasadena, he found discrepancies in Celeste and Bells so it was revised and then later revised again to correct. Please check computer files for revisions made to parts. ALWAYS USE Celeste and not bells which were cued in to part by NY Pops and are against the wishes of Johnny Mandel.
ROW.Performance_History: This version was prepared for and performed by the NY Pops. Performed by MF with Pasadena Pops in 2013 and in Palm Beach January 2015.
